Sequence
public class ForwardingFluentList<E>
extends AbstractEnumerable<E>
implements FluentList<E>

Wraps around any List implementation, and delegates all set methods to this delegateList .

array

public <T> T[] array(java.lang.Class<T> clazz)
Description copied from interface: ExtendedCollection
Similar to the method toArray, but receives no args and is type safe. Also, the returned array is just a copy. Note that the class is necessary, as Generics by themselves cannot solve this problem alone. For more info: http://www.ibm.com/developerworks/java/library/j-jtp01255.html

Specified by:
array in interface ExtendedCollection<E>
Returns:
A copy of the list as an array.

Returns a new list that is a one-dimensional flattening of this list (recursively). This means: for every element that is a list, extract its elements into the new array.
